    "body": "### Problem\n\nEven when calling `vim.lsp.completion.enable(false)` for a specific LSP, its completions are still funneled to `vim.lsp.omnifunc()`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nMinimal `repro.lua` config:\n\n```lua\nfor name, url in pairs {\n  \"https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig\",\n} do\n  local install_path = vim.fn.fnamemodify('nvim_issue/' .. name, ':p')\n  if vim.fn.isdirectory(install_path) == 0 then\n    vim.fn.system { 'git', 'clone', '--depth=1', url, install_path }\n  end\n  vim.opt.runtimepath:append(install_path)\nend\n\nvim.lsp.enable(\"jdtls\")\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"LspAttach\", {\n  group = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup(\"lsp_completion_disable\", {}),\n  callback = function(event)\n    local client = assert(vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(event.data.client_id))\n    if client.name == \"jdtls\" then\n      -- Disable `jdtls` completions. If other LSPs are attached, they can\n      -- continue to provide completions via the `vim.lsp.omnifunc()`.\n      vim.lsp.completion.enable(false, client.id, event.buf)\n    end\n  end,\n})\n```\n\nOpen a Java file with `nvim --clean -u repro.lua Main.java`, type `System.`, then trigger omni-completion with `<C-X><C-O>`. The JDT LS completions are still provided. Problem occurs with other LSPs, too.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe LSP omnicompletion should not provide completions for LSPs that had completion explicitly disabled.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-f8a56a8\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 26.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.16.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from repo",
