            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`vim.lsp.completion.enable(false)` only controls the `vim.lsp.completion.get()` + autotrigger, it doesn't touch omnifunc. `vim.lsp.omnifunc()` serves any client that advertises completion, regardless of that flag. If you want jdtls to stop completing entirely, just disable its completion capability on attach instead:\n\n```lua\nif client.name == \"jdtls\" then\n  client.server_capabilities.completionProvider = nil\nend\n```",
