        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`enable()`  isn't just an autotrigger toggle. It also registers the client for `vim.lsp.completion.get()` and sets up\n `CompleteDone ` (snippet + additionalTextEdits). autotrigger only adds the auto completion on the server's triggerCharacters. So `enable(true, …, {autotrigger=false})` still gives you `get() + CompleteDone`. And on `enable(false, …)` the opts are ignored, so autotrigger there is moot.\n\nAlso, omnifunc doesn't call `get()`. `get()` reads the enabled set (buf_handles[buf].clients) and does honor enable(false); omnifunc calls `vim.lsp.get_clients({method='textDocument/completion'})` directly and hits every capable client. \n\nSo `enable()` isn't redundant with autotrigger. Whether omnifunc should also honor the enabled set is a separate design call, for now, dropping the client's completionProvider capability...",
