            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> but isn't it kind of weird that omnifunc() doesn't use completeion.get() ...?\n\n`get()` only uses clients you've `enable(true)'d (buf_handles)`, while omnifunc grabs every completion capable client via `lsp.get_clients`. omnifunc is auto wired on LspAttach, so routing it through `get()` would break `<C-X><C-O>` for anyone who never called enable().",
