        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`omnifunc` gets auto set on attach `lsp._set_defaults()` without `enable()` ever being called, so the enabled set (buf_handles) is empty out of box, maybe that's why it uses `get_clients()` and not `get()` 🤔. routing it through `get()` would mean nothing completes until you `enable(true)` first. \n\ni'm guessing that's intentional so omnicompletion works out of the box, instead of making users add an `enable()` call in `LspAttach` just to get <C-X><C-O> working 😯",
            "created_at": "2026-06-03T10:29:37Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40068#issuecomment-4611396555",
